JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 114
IS  - 4
SP  - 1399
EP  - 1436
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - In the 1980s several countries with large government debt or deficit implemented substantial, and in some cases drastic, deficit cuts. Contrary to widespread expectations, in many cases private consumption boomed rather than contracted. This paper shows that in times of “fiscal stress” shocks to government revenues and, especially, expenditure have very different effects on private consumption than in “normal” times.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355399556304
